The paper deals with the design of LDPC codes for the block-fading channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of iterative decoding also suggests a possible connection to network information theory (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The comparison with multiplexed parallel turbo codes suggests a possible connection to coding theory (cs.CC). Finally, the practical applications of LDPC codes in communication systems suggest a possible connection to computer networks (cs.COM).
